survey_response.review_text: I underwent knees surgery .Dr Sharan Shivaraj Patil did the suregery successfully. After 6 weeks of surgery I am walking independently without walker and support of any body. The doctor has explained and instructed about the follow up activities after the surgery . Also the Doctor is courteous with the patients. Even physiotherapists also shown lot of concern and treated me well. Specifically the dedication of Sri Sanjay Poul physiotherapist in the hospital and in home service is highly appreciated. I thank Dr.Sharan Shivaraj Patil and his entire team for their wellbeing in treating me to my satisfaction.

Had difficulty in walking , pain , because of worn out knee joints.. so I got total knee replacement done at Sparsh 6 months ago.. Today I hv got life in to my life.. I go for  daily walk, indulge in all activities, won’t wait for lift but will climb stairs, etc.. Iam happy with Dr Sharan Patil’s SPARSH! SMILE! SKILL!  All doctors are dedicated to work , well trained Staff , good nursing care, excellent physiotherapy, . One has to bear with waiting time, as there are many needy patients like us. canteen is not upto mark.

The surgical team did a splendid job with my 90 year old mother’s hip joint fracture. And the nursing staff at Sparsh Infantry road was super. Always ready to ensure mom was comfortable and taken care. Hats off to the nursing team !!

It will be really good if the surgery team would communicate a little more with the patient & the family before and after the surgery. It will give a lot of comfort to the family.

The first day I waited over two hours only to see him for less than one minute when he says "please get an MRI". The second day I waited almost an hour and saw him for 5 minutes. In between I need to contact him about the MRI but the phone number I was given only connected to the exchange and nobody answered. I left a message asking for a call back at the OPD department and of course nobody called me. 
I did speak to a couple of junior doctors who were very good, attentive and respectful of my time. Dr Patil came highly recommended and I was very disappointed. His recommendation was that I "do physiotherapy sincerely" by which I can only assume he thinks I have not being doing physio for over 6 months, despite not asking me or knowing me at all. Could have spent my time so much better. Between the long lines at payment and fighting through Bangalore traffic and waiting for the doctor, I really would have been better off not seeing him.

I had a broken leg and i am expecting a surgery for internal fixation. My wife booked an appointment to see Dr. Sharan Patil at 1.40 PM so that she can consult and get his opinion.Firstly Doctor didn't show up for about an hour saying he was on rounds and later went for lunch. The OPD staff was calling us 20 min prior to the appointment asking if we are coming for the appointment and when we showed up before time the Dr is not there for an hour.Secondly his assistants came and took all the reports from wife saying that the nurse will give it back to her.Dr. Sharan came after an hour's wait and didn't even spend 5 min to speak with my wife saying there is no need for surgery and it will heal on its own. My wife was literally walking and talking to Dr he didn't even have time to sit and talk to my wife patiently. When my wife insisted him to provide proper guideline he just denied saying i don't treat reports i treat patients. Without even considering that a person with Broken leg can't visit every doctor for an opinion.Last but not the least and biggest bummer is when the nurse returned all the reports to my wife they had lost one of my prescriptions. Now they are not able to find it and without that i can't claim my bills with insurance company.I would say there is no empathy towards patients and very bad management.

**** ***** *** ******** ******** *** ******* ******* **** *** * also it takes 4 to 5 hrs to complete consultation.
Staffs those who are coordinating won’t respond properly.Main thing Dr Sharan Patil doesn’t have time to talk to the patient. Reply’s are give by junior trainee doctor. ***** ***** **** ***************** ** ******* ***** ***** ** **** *** ***** ******** **** **** **** ***** ** *********

I was having severe pain in my knees. I had lot of apprehensions regarding surgery.  Dr.Sharan Patil cleared all my doubts. He was very friendly,  highly positive and assured complete recovery.  Meeting him built confidence and courage in me.  
Surgery was done successfully and now I am back to normal  walking independently .  My gratitude and regards to Dr. Sharan Patil.

Dr Sharan Patil comes across as someone who is very approachable  and his excellent  bedside manner instills immense confidence in the patient, 
thereby contributing to  a sure and speedy recovery 
I wish him nothing but the very best in all his future endeavors 
Indira Basapa

But  even after  undergoing physiotherapy regularly for seven months  I am not in a position  to walk comfortably. I am limping while walking  and getting pain.  I am really  unhappy.
